.TH ANGLERFI.SH 1 "2026-07-18" "anglerfish" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
anglerfi.sh, af \- unified package manager wrapper for offensive security toolchains
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B anglerfi.sh
.RB { \-i | \-\-install }
.I package\fR|\fImeta
.RB [ \-v | \-\-version
.IR ver ]
.RI [ \- pkg " ...] [" + pkg " ...]"
.br
.B anglerfi.sh
.RB { \-r | \-\-remove }
.I package\fR|\fImeta
.br
.B anglerfi.sh
.RB { \-l | \-\-list }
.RB [ \-a | \-all | \-\-all ]
.br
.B anglerfi.sh
.B \-\-firewall
.RB { desktop | server }
.br
.B anglerfi.sh
.RB { \-s | \-\-setup }
.br
.B anglerfi.sh
.RB { \-h | \-\-help }
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B anglerfi.sh
wraps
.BR apt (8),
\fBgo install\fR, \fBpipx\fR, \fBgit\fR, and one-off hash-verified downloads
behind a single CLI and one editable JSON catalog
.RI ( package.json ),
so installing, listing, and removing an offensive security toolset is one
consistent
command regardless of which underlying package manager a given tool
actually uses.
.PP
The script only elevates the specific commands that need root
(\fBapt-get\fR, writes under \fB/opt\fR or \fB/etc\fR, \fBiptables\fR) via
.BR sudo (8),
prompting for a password only when it actually hits one of those. Everything
else, including \fBgo install\fR, runs as the invoking user.
.PP
When installed via the \fB.deb\fR, the catalog lives at
\fI/etc/anglerfish/package.json\fR (a conffile, so local edits survive
upgrades) and both it and \fI/usr/bin/anglerfi.sh\fR are root-owned. The
script refuses to run any privileged action, and refuses to run at all if
it carries the setuid or setgid bit, unless both the script and the
catalog it's using are owned by root and not group/other-writable \(em
this is enforced at runtime, not just at install time.
.B af
is a plain symlink to \fBanglerfi.sh\fR shipped by the \fB.deb\fR, for
less typing.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-install \ \fIpackage\fR|\fImeta\fR
Install a single package, or every member of a named \fBmeta\fR group from
the catalog.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version \ \fIver\fR
Pin or override the version to install. Only valid when exactly one
package ends up being installed after any \fB\-pkg\fR/\fB+pkg\fR are
applied \(em rejected for anything that resolves to more or fewer than
one package, and for \fBmanual\fR-kind installs (those are hash-pinned to
one specific artifact; edit \fIpackage.json\fR for a different release).
For \fBapt\fR this becomes \fIname\fR=\fIver\fR; for \fBgo\fR it rewrites
the \fI@version\fR suffix; for \fBpipx\fR it forces a reinstall
(\fB\-\-force\fR) at that pin, bypassing the normal "already installed"
skip so it can also downgrade.
.TP
.RI \- pkg
When installing a \fBmeta\fR group, drop \fIpkg\fR from the members that
would otherwise be installed. Can be repeated. Rejected against a single
(non-meta) package.
.TP
.RI + pkg
When installing a \fBmeta\fR group, install \fIpkg\fR in addition to the
group's members for this run only, without editing \fIpackage.json\fR. If
\fIpkg\fR is itself the name of a meta group, every one of its members is
added instead (so several meta groups can be merged into a single run).
Can be repeated. Rejected against a single (non-meta) package.
.IP
\fB\-pkg\fR and \fB+pkg\fR can be combined and given in any order: the
full set (target group plus every added group/package) is assembled first,
then every exclusion is subtracted from that combined set, and the result
is deduplicated \(em so excluding a package that only exists because of a
\fB+meta\fR addition still removes it, regardless of where the flags fall
on the command line.
.TP
.BR \-r ", " \-\-remove \ \fIpackage\fR|\fImeta\fR
Remove a single package, or every member of a named \fBmeta\fR group.
.TP
.BR \-l ", " \-\-list \ [ \-a | \-all | \-\-all ]
List packages from the catalog and whether each is currently installed.
Without \fB\-a\fR/\fB\-\-all\fR, only installed packages are shown.
.TP
.B \-\-firewall \ {desktop|server}
Configure \fBiptables\fR via \fBiptables-persistent\fR: deny all inbound
except loopback and established connections, plus 8000/8080
(\fBdesktop\fR) or 22 (\fBserver\fR).
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-setup
Install the \fBgo\fR, \fBpipx\fR, \fBgit\fR, and \fBcargo\fR toolchains
needed by the corresponding catalog kinds.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show usage and exit.
.SH THE CATALOG
\fIpackage.json\fR has a \fBmeta\fR section (named bundles of package
names) and one section per install kind:
.TP
.B apt
A thin wrapper around \fBapt-get install\fR. An optional \fBpre_install\fR
command runs once before the install, for vendors that ship their own apt
repository (GPG key + sources entry) instead of living in the default
Debian/Ubuntu repos.
.TP
.B go
Wraps \fBgo install\fR \fImodule\fR@\fIversion\fR.
.TP
.B pipx
Wraps \fBpipx install\fR for Python CLI tools, kept out of the system
\fBpip\fR.
.TP
.B git
Shallow-clones (\fB\-\-depth 1\fR) a repository into \fI/opt/\fIname\fR,
optionally at a pinned ref, then runs a \fBpost_clone\fR command. No hash
pinning \(em intended for tools meant to track upstream via their own
update mechanism.
.TP
.B manual
For anything with no package manager: downloads an artifact, verifies it
against a pinned sha256 \fBhash\fR before unpacking or symlinking anything,
then runs \fBpost_install\fR.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/anglerfish/package.json
The tool catalog, when installed via the \fB.deb\fR (root-owned conffile).
.TP
.I package.json
Catalog fallback when the script is run from a source checkout, or when
\fBANGLERFISH_PKG\fR is unset.
.TP
.I /var/lib/anglerfish/installed.list
.TQ
.I $XDG_STATE_HOME/anglerfish/installed.list
Install log (root's when run as root, the invoking user's otherwise).
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B ANGLERFISH_PKG
Overrides the catalog path. Ignored for any privileged action unless it
too is root-owned and not group/other-writable \(em pointing this at an
attacker-writable file cannot be used to run arbitrary privileged
commands.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B anglerfi.sh \-i nmap
Install a single apt-backed package.
.TP
.B anglerfi.sh \-i nmap \-v 7.94
Pin a specific apt version.
.TP
.B anglerfi.sh \-i web
Install everything in the \(dqweb\(dq meta group.
.TP
.B anglerfi.sh \-i web \-zaproxy +burpsuite\-pro
Install the \(dqweb\(dq group, skipping zaproxy, plus burpsuite\-pro.
.TP
.B anglerfi.sh \-i web +infra +osint
Merge three meta groups into a single run.
.TP
.B anglerfi.sh \-l \-\-all
Show the full catalog with installed/missing status.
.TP
.B anglerfi.sh \-\-firewall desktop
Lock down inbound traffic except 8000/8080.
.SH SECURITY CONSIDERATIONS
The catalog is trusted configuration, not user input: every
\fBinstall\fR/\fBpost_install\fR/\fBpre_install\fR/\fBpost_clone\fR/\fBremove\fR/\fBcheck\fR
field runs as root when a privileged action needs it. Treat it like
\fI/etc/sudoers\fR.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR apt-get (8),
.BR sudo (8),
.BR iptables (8)
.SH AUTHOR
zyg0th
